@LAPhill was thinking of you today while doing some “scoring” for my wedding video (DIY slideshow / iPhone video montage.) 

I loaded up Keyscape cinematic grand, Spitfire BBC Orch on 4 tracks, (violins, violas, cellos, horns,) and went at like I would a vocal arrangement- one voice at a time, which was great for internal voice leading and lead to some beautiful & unexpected chords. 

Came together really fast too.

@kylem Yeah, Keyscape is an excellent choice with some truly excellent sampled instruments, though a bit of an up-front investment ($400).

In fact, I just spent the last fifteen minutes practicing piano with Keyscape before taking a break here on the DIscord. It must be a decade old at this point, but Spectrasonics do a good job at supporting it. They're constantly patching it and a few months ago they added a fully-sampled felt piano instrument that sounds excellent.

Kontakt wouldn't be a bad investment either, since it's the backbone of NI's entire business model at this point, it comes with a sizeable sample library (not just piano), and new sample instruments are constantly being developed for the platform.
